0_1	0.0	The report, issued by the U.S.
0_2	0.36363636363636365	Department of Housing and Urban Development, shows that a record number of working-poor families -- at least 5.4 million of them -- were paying more than half their income for housing or living in substandard conditions in 1997, the freshest figures available.
0_3	0.0	That's an increase of 12 percent since 1991.
